{
  "stem": "14737.2",
  "chunk_idx": 0,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 10.2,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "After I have graduated the gymnasium, in 1936 in June the 16, I went to Brno, to medical school.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Why did I choose Brno?",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "This was the second largest city in Czechoslovakia.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Brno had a medical school where was a lot of privileges which I could have there since my father couldn't afford to send me to university, despite the university was completely free, but over there to live there someplace and that.",
      "word_count": 41
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Brno had a very, very large community, Jewish community, and very favorable to students who wanted to study.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "Brno was a town where a lot of pretty wealthy Jews lived there.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And in their community, they made two things.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "Number one, they had a special building which for Jewish students or for orphans who cannot afford, they can live there.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "Now, there was three, four, five in a room.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Now, on Brno, in the street [INAUDIBLE], number 31, this was this building, a five, six-story building.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "It was an orphanage home for people who [INAUDIBLE].",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And there was a studentheim and was also [NON-ENGLISH] also there.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And that quite a big one, because not only students ate there from who went to university who couldn't afford, but also poor people.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Everyone to come there to eat lunch had a free lunch.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "Now, coming in a town, no questions were asked to the line and went in.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "Wouldn't say that lunch was the best, but it was a little.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So now if you have something like this, you have a place where to sleep and you have a place where to eat, so already it's not-- I didn't have to, have to pay tuition.",
      "word_count": 35
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "This was convenient for a student who couldn't afford, especially me.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And so I went to Brno and lived there.",
      "word_count": 9
    }
  ],
